	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><strong>Illusory Image</strong></p><p>Roll an &amp;Reference[illusoryimages]{illusion check} for this spell.</p><ul><li><p>You create an illusory duplicate of yourself at a location within range that you have seen before, regardless of obstacles. The image looks and sounds like you but is intangible. If the illusion takes damage, the spell ends.</p></li><li><p>You can use your Action to move the image up to twice your speed, and make it gesture, speak, and behave as you choose. It mimics your mannerisms perfectly.</p></li><li><p>You can see through the imageâ€™s eyes and hear through its ears as if you were in its space. On your turn, you may use a Bonus Action to switch between its senses and your own. While using its senses, you are &amp;reference[blinded] and &amp;reference[deafened] to your own surroundings.</p></li><li><p>Physical interaction reveals the image to be an illusion, as creatures and objects pass through it.</p></li><li><p>A creature may use its Action to examine the image. On a successful &amp;reference[Investigation] check against your spell save DC, the creature recognizes the illusion. To it, the image appears translucent and its sounds are hollow.</p></li></ul>",
